C. TRUST ESTATES OF DECEASED OBLIGORS  
1. Claim 
A person who may have a claim against the trust is a 
creditor,  and  must file  a  claim  to  demand  payment 
for a liability of the decedent. (
Prob. Code 
§   19000, et seq.). 
a. Notice to Creditors 
The  trustee  is  required  to  give  notice  to  known  
creditors of   the settlor (decedent). (
