b. Time for Filing Claims 
A  creditor  must  file  a  claim  within  four  months  
after the first publication of   notice to creditors or 
60  days  after  the  date  actual  notice  is  mailed  or  
personally  delivered  to  the  creditor,  whichever  
occurs later. (
Prob. Code § 19100(a)). 
c. Documentation 
