b. Requesting  an  appropriate  court  set  a  date,  
time and place for a hearing; 
c. Making   a   reasonable   effort   to   obtain   all   
relevant  information,  including  information  
concerning the parties’ income and property; 
d. Within  14  days  (exclusive  of  weekends  and  
legal  holidays)  after  receipt  of  written  notice  
in  a  record  from  an  initiating,  responding  or  
registering court, sending a copy of the notice 
to the petitioner; 
